====Reconstruction notes====
Various inflected or derived verbal forms which were written phonetically, e.g. {{m|oko|乎}} or {{m|oko|兮}}, testify beyond doubt that this word had initial {{IPAfont|*/h-/}} and is the ancestor of Middle Korean {{okm-inline|ᄒᆞ다〮|hò-tá}}. It is usually transcribed as *HO- after the Middle Korean reflex, but the Middle Korean irregular infinitive {{okm-inline|ᄒᆞ〮야〮|hóy-á}} implies that the earlier form was actually {{IPAfont|*hoy-}} ({{ko-ref|Vovin 2010}}, p.27). Whether the attested Old Korean forms transcribed older {{IPAfont|*hoy-}} or later {{IPAfont|*ho-}} is unclear due to the phonological opaqueness of the orthography.

